    JavaRDD<Text> rows = elements.mapPartitions(generateKeys)
        .flatMap(pair -> {
              if (null == pair.getSecond()) {return Arrays.asList(pair.getFirst()).iterator();}
              else {return Arrays.asList(pair.getFirst(), pair.getSecond()).iterator();}
        })
        .map(key -> key.getRow());

This RDD can now be sampled using `.sample()` and then collected to a local list. This list can then be used to set the split points on the table. It may be necessary to count the number of rows to determine an appropriate sampling proportion so that approximately the right number of split points can be sampled.

