We have a [federated rest api](https://github.com/gchq/gaffer-tools/tree/master/federated-rest) in gaffer-tools, but it would also be useful to have a federated gaffer store.

This store would hold a list of Graphs. 
Each operation would be executed on each graph and the results would be merged together.

All operations (including the core operations like Min and Max) would need a new Operation Handler that delegates the query to all of the configured Graphs and merges the result. Perhaps create a abstract handler - FederatedOperationHandler that does all the delegation then the handlers would just have to deal with taking a List of results and merging them together. 

e.g
```java
public abstract class FederatedOperationHandler<OP extends Output<O>, O> implements OutputOperationHandler<OP, O> {
    @Override
    public O doOperation(final OP operation, final Context context, final Store store) throws OperationException {
        final List<Graph> graphs = store.getGraphs();
        final List<O> results = new ArrayList<O>(graphs.size());
        for (final Graph graph : graphs) {
            results.add(graph.execute(operation, context.getUser()));
        }

        return mergeResults(results, operation, context, store);
    }

    protected abstract O mergeResults(final List<O> results, final OP operation, final Context context, final Store store);
}



public class MaxHandler extends FederatedOperationHandler<Max, Element> {
    @Override
    protected Element mergeResults(final List<Element> results, final Max operation, final Context context, final Store store) {
        return Collections.max(results, operation.getCombinedComparator());
    }
}

public class GetElementsHandler extends FederatedOperationHandler<GetElements, CloseableIterable<? extends Element>> {
    @Override
    protected CloseableIterable<? extends Element> mergeResults(final List<CloseableIterable<? extends Element>> results, final GetElements operation, final Context context, final Store store) {
        // Concatenate all the results into 1 iterable
        return new ChainedIterable<>(results);
    }
}

```

