All classes which implement toString(), equals() and hashCode() in the Gaffer codebase should do in a consistent way. We have chosen the Apache Commons Lang style for use throughout the project.

Classes which implement these methods should contain implementations similar to that described below:

```java
    @Override
    public boolean equals(final Object obj) {
        if (this == obj) {
            return true;
        }

        if (obj == null || getClass() != obj.getClass()) {
            return false;
        }

        final MyObject myObj = (MyObject) obj;

        return new EqualsBuilder()
                .append(field1, myObj.field1)
                .append(field2, myObj.field2)
                .isEquals();
    }

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return new HashCodeBuilder(17, 37)
                .append(field1)
                .append(field2)
                .toHashCode();
    }

    @Override
