The `HyperLogLogPlusAggregator` only works with sketches where `p = 5` and `sp = 5`.

This behaviour can be seen by changing the two instances of `new HyperLogLogPlus(5, 5)` in the `setup` method of `HyperLogLogPlusAggregatorTest` to `new HyperLogLogPlus(6, 6)`. The test then fails.

The problem is caused by the following line in `HyperLogLogPlusAggregator`:

    if (null == sketch) {
        sketch = new HyperLogLogPlus(5, 5);
    }

As the `sketch` variable is always null after the aggregator is initialised, this means that the first sketch to be aggregated is merged into the `HyperLogLogPlus` with parameters 5 and 5. If the sketch to be merged in has different parameters then it fails with a `java.lang.RuntimeException: An Exception occurred when trying to aggregate the HyperLogLogPlus objects`.

To fix this, when the first sketch is merged in, the sketch variable should be set to a clone of the first sketch.

